nodes.title: Basic usage
widgets_values:
## Usage

| Usage | (Number key) Shortcuts |
|---|---|
| 1. Set Checkpoints, Clip + VAE | (3) Checkpoint (subgraph) |
| 2. (optional) add LoRAs | (1) Settings, Prompt, Image, Video |
| 3. Enable Featuras you want with the "Features - Switch" | (1) Settings, Prompt, Image, Video |
| 4. Tune any parameter to your liking under "BASIC SETTINGS" | |
| 5. Add images you need | |
| 6. Write your prompts | |
| 7. Generate | |
|Optional: Tune any internal setting | (2) Backend (subgraph) |

nodes.title: BASIC settings
widgets_values:
| Setting | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | **Seconds** | 5 | Set the desired length of the video in seconds. | | **CRF** | 20, webm, VP9 | Video compression level. Visually lossless. Set on VHS Node.| | **FPS** | 16 | Frames per second for videos. Use 24 for faster motion/shorter videos. | | **Shift** | 5 | Default 5. Adjust and test; WAN 2.2 valid in range 5‚Äì8. | | **Steps total** | 4 | Total steps - node handles step math. More steps ‚Üí higher quality but longer generation. Use even numbers. | | **Step Refiner** | 2 | Default 2 (50% of 4). Change to test different swap behavior. | | **CFG** | 1.0 | Controls prompt adherence. Use 1-1.5. 1 disables/ignores the negative prompt. 1.0 is needed for speed-up's like 4/8-step models/LoRAs | | **Sampler** | euler | "Euler" works everytime. Other samplers can enhance detail or motion. This has major impact on how the video is generated. | | **Scheduler** | simple | "Simple" works eveytime. Other like "beta" and others can enhance some samplers. | | **Seed** | number + randomize | Random outcome every run. Set a specific seed to reproduce the same outcome. | | **Sage Attention** | disabled | Can be enabled **if installed correctly** to speed-up video generation times. | | **Watermark upload** | none | Here you can upload a watermark image and calibrate the settings to your liking (subgraph). | | **Positive prompt** | none | Write your positive prompt!
1) Brief description of the setting/appearance
2) Actions, motions, story
3) Camera composition
CFG 1 normally disables/ignores the negative prompt! NAG effectively enables negative prompting on CFG 1.| | **Negative prompt** | none | Write what you would like to exclude. Works only if CFG > 1 or NAG is enabled | | **Checkpoints** | Safetensors/GGUf |Choose the type of Checkpoint to use. Wan 2.2 uses a different diffusion model for the first steps (high noise) vs the last steps (low noise). You can ether use safetensors or gguf.| | **VAE** | same as WAN 2.1 | Still using the same VAE as WAN 2.1. | | **CLIP** | standard encoder | Use your preferred standard CLIP text encoder. No CLIP Vision H ‚Äî not trained/implemented in WAN 2.2 and weights are disabled. | | **Upscaler model** | any | The optional used model for Upsscaling /w model. A downloaded upscaling-model is needed. |

nodes.title: Features
widgets_values:
| Feature | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | **NAG** | off | This will use your negative condition and concat it with the standard WAN AI negative prompt for convenience.
If you do not want this, just disable the standard negative node.
‚ö†Ô∏èNAG needs a lot of VRAM, so if you do not need this. Just let it be disabled. | | **FLF2V** | off | This enables the usage of a "First-Last-Frame to video". The video will start with the 1st frame and end with the last frame. Both must be set/uploaded. | | **Color match** | off | This will try to match the color from the initial image to the samples. The color match algorithms default is set by default to '0.75'. Feel free to test other strength. | | **Perfect loop** | off | This must be used with FLF2V and the same initial image and last-frame image. It will try to find the seamless frame to loop back to the start and blending frames together. üí° Best used with "color match". | | **Interpolation** | off | This will interpolate your video to double fps at the end. Interpolated FPS = 2 √ó FPS. | | **Upscale 2x (fast)** | off | Final resolution = 2 √ó start resolution while maintaining aspect ratio. No morph; color-correct fast lanczos upscale. Low VRAM consumption. | | **Upscale /w Model (slow)** | off | Final resolution depends on the used upscaler model; Can change/enhance details and high VRAM consumption. | | **Watermark** | off | Enable for a watermark overlay on video. | | **Extract Last Frame** | off | Enable to extract the last frame of the video as image. | | **MiniMeme** | off | This will create a mini gif from your video down scaled by 5 for meme's or discord. | | **SageAttention** | off | Needs to be installed! Possibly accelerates generation. | | **FP16 accumulation** | on | Adds computational speed and memory efficiency |

üéûÔ∏è The last frame of you final result.

This will always select the last run method, even if you selected multiple options! (Interpolation node > FLF2V node > i2v only)

The image will be saved on the same folder as your video.
You can start with this again to expand your video.

nodes.title: Resolution note
widgets_values:
### Automatic scaling and resolution calculation The initial image will be scaled on optimized math targeting a WAN 2.2 VAE (div16) resolution. Aspect will be calculated automatically and the video resolution will be set to the nearest possible match with the megapixel count. | Stage | Target MP | Quality | Use case | |---:|---:|---:|---| | 1 | 0.25 | Preview
~ 360p| Motion/physics tests. | | 2 | 0.33 | Fast
~ 432p| Simple quality. | | 3 | 0.40 | SD Speed
~ 480p| "Sweet spot" for speed. | | 4 | 0.60 | SD
~ 576p| Optimal for mobile-first content. | | 5 | 0.72 | Balanced HD
~ 640p| Consistent, good details. | | 6 | 0.85 | HD
~ 720p| Very stable, crisp details. | | 7 | 1.05 | THD
~ 768p| Maximum stability for Image-to-Video. | | 8 | 1.15 | THD+
~ 800p| 16GB VRAM "sweet spot". 16fps/5s | | 9 | 1.30 | HQ
~ 900p| High detail, very slow (Requires high VRAM). | | 10 | 2.07 | FHD
~ 1080p| Production grade detail, extreme slow (Requires very high VRAM). |

nodes.title: Seconds and frames
widgets_values:
The optimal frame count is calculated automatically based on input seconds.

* **16 FPS** - 5 seconds are native. After that WAN 2.2 starts looping back
* **24 FPS** - 3 seconds are native. After that WAN 2.2 starts looping back.

Both equals the standard frame length of WAN 2.2.
